NIB pistol. 

The lowest price I have seen for these online starts is and auction starting at $980 with a buy now price of $1050.

For sale is a brand new Sphinx SDP Compact Alpha w/ threaded barrel. The gun comes with 2-15 round magazines and adjustable polymer grips.

The SPHINX SDP Compact Alpha is a duty-sized pistol that can adapt to virtually any role. Every design feature on the SDP Compact Alpha is tailored to maximize performance, quality, and ergonomics. The competition inspired trigger is very smooth with a clean break and short, crisp, reset. The steel slide is machined from billet and is hand fitted to mate perfectly with the interior, full length guide rails, of the billet aluminum upper frame. The polymer pistol grip features interchangeable back-straps to adjust length and width of the grip, the grip inserts are specifically designed to maximize contact with the support hand for added control. Also for added control, the high trigger guard shape and beaver tail allow for high hand placement on the pistol frame to compliment the low bore axis of the barrel, which allow the shooters to easily manage recoil. A Picatinny rail on the frame allow for the addition of modern tactical shooting accessories. The front and rear cocking serrations offer different options of firearm manipulation and the dotted front sight contrasts with the black rear sight for quick target acquisition. Ambidextrous features include the decocking lever and a magazine release that can be switched to either side. The slide release lever also serves as the take-down pin and is located on the left side of the Compact Alpha. Every component of the SDP Compact is manufactured to the highest standards and tolerances are extremely tight. Derived from competition and built for duty use, the SDP Compact is the ideal gun to suit your needs on the job, in the home, or in the shoot box.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rifle Marksmanship, basic, intermediate.
postcontent:
If you want to learn to shoot for hunting, target or just to get a young one confident enough to handle a firearm, I am willing to help. I do this for friends locally already, and I decided I enjoy it and why not try to help more people. And with all these guys building AR's these days, I see a lot of basic mistakes at the range. Don't learn bad habits!

What you can learn with me:
-First and foremost safety. This is really important for younger shooters to learn early.
-Rifle, carbine or full length. AR platform is my bread and butter. I can also do shotgun, crossbow.
-Basic weapon handling, maintaining, and comfortably engaging from distances of 5 yards to whatever the range has. Usually they max out at 3-500 yards. 

I prefer my favored range in Garrettsville. But if you have a range you would like to use, I will meet you if its not too far from my home location. of Canfield.
When: 
I am available Monday/Wednesday/Friday mornings from range open till early afternoon when I have to head to work. If you need a specific day, I can see what I can do. 
About me:
I am a 30 year old USMC Infantry veteran with 7 expert rifle qualifications. I have experience instructing basic entry level to intermediate rifle techniques, as well as close quarters drills. I can provide all of my credentials on request of course.

postcontent:
Have a Finnish made model 1891 Mosin.  Manufactured 1942 by VKT, D Chamber to accept standard 7.62x54r.  Hex receiver, Finn Hangers.  Period green leather sling and bayonet included (not pictured).  Good rifling, not counter-bored.

Hex Receiver, barrel, and bolt numbers all match....not forced matched, not Finn matched.  Just matching original.  The magazine is not marked, the butt plate is marked with a (strange font) different number.  

Item is complete, including cleaning rod and barrel band retaining screws.  Bore in good shape, as is the Finnish 2 piece stock.  Blade sight has been drifted for bayonet free point of aim shooting.  

Stock is marked Finnish Civil Guard/Home Guard ('S' with crown) just forward of the magazine.
